snippet: Elizabeth Warren, the newly elected Democratic senator from Massachusetts, will become a member of the very club that sought to block her from leading the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau.
abstract: Elizabeth Warren, newly elected Democratic senator from Massachusetts, will become a member of the very club whose Republican members sought to block her from leading the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, which she created in 2010; she has sent mixed signals on how she will approach her job and interact with Republican senators that spurned her.
lead_paragraph: Elizabeth Warren, the newly elected Democratic senator from Massachusetts, will become a member of the very club that sought to block her from leading the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau.

headline.seo: Elizabeth Warren, Known, and Maybe Feared, on National Stage
headline.main: A New Senator, Known Nationally and Sometimes Feared
headline.print_headline: A New Senator, Known Nationally and Sometimes Feared
